history.content:
Swap is for changing classes, not for changing sections.

Options is for changing sections within a class you are enrolled for.

There is no way to change sections for a class you are waitlisted for, other than dropping/reenrolling in the class.

children.subject:
It is an unfortunate feature to lose (and I hope it is brought back), but it is not a bug in the new system that you cannot change sections for a class you are waitlisted for.

Your TAs are mistaken; perhaps they were thinking of how Telebears used to work.

I think you've misunderstood me. I was enrolled in the class, not waitlisted. And the confirmation page said exactly what I wanted to do and cal central let the swap process but for some reason it dropped me out of the class.  Also, I'm waiting for a response from Michael-David Sasson, so I want to leave the discussion unresolved.

Ah, yes, I did misread your post twice; apologies.

It seems likely though that the issue is that you used Swap, which, again, is designed to change classes, not sections.

UPDATE: I've dropped the current waitlist section I was placed in after the failed swap and enrolled in a new section with only 1 person on the waitlist. Just to confirm, the only waitlist that matters is the discussion/lab one, not the lecture one right?

I think you can do it either way as I've used swap to change sections within a class for another class and it worked fine and I was originally already enrolled in the class, not waitlisted. Also, the TAs I asked told me that it should've went through and that this was a common bug on Cal Central.

history.content: So i was enrolled in the cs61a class, lecture and lab, and then today, I tried swapping lab sections on Cal Central into a waitlisted lab section and I used the swap option but for some reason it took me out of the class entirely and into the waitlist even for lecture even though I used the swap option (normally, it should keep you in the current section and put you on the waitlist for the other but it dropped my current section for some reason) so I think there's an error in the cal central enrollment system. I talked to some of the course TAs and they agreed that there was a bug in the system and advised me to post here to get the administration to fix this issue. Is there anything else I can do?
